This fixture is a NEGATIVE regression (0.3.0.29 interface-value keystone, Crumb S1): a `struct`
that nominally conforms to an interface is passed where the interface VALUE type is expected. A
struct is pure value data with no stable address to back a fat pointer, so it does NOT up-cast into
the contract (resolve.tks) — the checker rejects it with a NAMED honest-stop that points the user at
the two surfaces that DO dispatch a struct's contract: make the implementer a `class`, or take it by
a generic `<T: Reader>` bound (static dispatch). Interface-value boxing of a struct is deferred to
the safety spine (docs/design/interface-value-type.md §4).

